Noticed this during the code review for PHP-1063 (cursor refactoring for 1.6): https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-php-driver/pull/737#discussion_r18112088

When a cursor query is executed, we perform a string comparison:

{code}
strcmp(".$cmd", cursor->ns+(strlen(cursor->ns)-5))
{code}

{{cursor->ns}} may come from the second MongoCursor argument, and it's quite possible for a valid namespace to be smaller than 5 characters (e.g. "a.b"). This means we may end up reading bytes before the memory address pointed to by {{cursor->ns}}.

